article.headline: N.J. Tech 72, Houston Baptist 66
article.story: HOUSTON -- Chris Flores scored 28 points and New Jersey Tech defeated Houston Baptist 72-66 on Thursday night. Flores sank four 3-pointers to pace 39.1 percent 3-point shooting by the Highlanders (12-12, 6-1 Great West Conference), who won their fifth game in a row. Isaiah Wilkerson added 16 points. Andrew Gonzalez scored 29 points but missed eight 3-pointers and committed eight turnovers for the Huskies (3-22, 2-7), whose losing streak reached four. Terry Bembry contributed 10 points. The Highlanders outscored the Huskies 14-3 over the last 3:35. New Jersey Tech, which outrebounded Houston Baptist 38-27, swept the season series.
